external_knowledge:
- The problem score is a measure of the severity of issues with a particular size, with higher scores indicating more significant problems;
- The fit test success rate is a measure of how well a size performs in fit tests, with higher rates indicating better performance;
- Inverse of the success rate is calculated as 1 - success rate.

sql:
SELECT test_date, test_results
FROM fit_tests
WHERE tested_by = 0;

SELECT COUNT(test_id) AS total_fit_tests
FROM fit_tests
WHERE tested_by = 0;

SELECT size_id, COUNT(*) AS total_fit_tests
FROM fit_tests
GROUP BY size_id;
